    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A pen point is the tip of a pen that touches the writing surface and distributes ink from a reservoir in the pen or adhering to the tip itself. The design may vary, including a simple tip, a split tip, a ball point, a stylograph, or another design.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
